<br>
Each class has an easy mob that spawns somewhere in the western part of the zone which will drop your gloves,bracer,hat, and arms at random.  Each class shares their mob with another class.  So for example I think the unicorns drop mage and wizard gear?  Something like that<br>
<br>
You get your pants and your BP/Robe from a random drop off of a harder mob (usually level 54 to 60) that spawns on the eastern side of the zone somewhere.  For mages I think it is the moving flowers or the little wooden guys.  I can't remember but I think I do remember that they spawn mostly in the northern part of the zone.<br>
<br>
In addition to that the named treants always drop a random BP/robe for any class.  The baby treants sometimes drop random legs for any class.  Furthermore there are named mobs that are basically just bigger versions of the mobs that spawn on the western side of the zone which wonder randomly that always drop arms or legs I think.<br>
<br>
You should have no problem soloing the mobs that drop the random hats/bracers/arms if you don't get adds.  The ones that drop the robes might be too tough.  The main problem with hunting the guys that drop the hats/bracers/arms is that there are some wondering named unicorns that are level 55 and might be too tough to solo.  They definately path along the western wall of the zone so if you set up your camp up there they will eventually wander into you.  I'd recommend setting up camp near the lake directly east of the zone-in.  Not sure if that would work but that is where I'd try to solo if I was going to solo there.  <br>
<br>
If you really want to get some mage armor I'd recommend soloing the bank area in keal.  I've seen every piece of silk quest armor drop there and it is very soloable by a mage and it has the exact same stats as the armor that drops in PoB.  If you spend enough time there you'll eventually get it all and would be much easier than PoG but you won't get those 100pp gem drops there like you do in PoG. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dolekinsoothesayer>Dolekin Soothesayer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.soldiers-of-light.net/phpBB2/images/avatars/gallery/Misc3/babykick.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#333333>(1/19/03 4:17:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ?</span><hr size=1> the flowers are too hard for a mage to solo.  They gate so easily, and whipe out whole raids when they do gate.  Mage wouldnt have enough mana to take it out.<br>
